<h2><a name="bool" id="bool">bool</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
The keyword bool is used to declare Boolean logic variables; that is, variables
which can be either true or false.
For example, the following code declares a boolean variable called done,
initializes it to false, and then loops until that variable is set to true.
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">     bool done <span class="sy0">=</span> <span class="kw2">false</span>;
     <span class="kw1">while</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="sy0">!</span>done <span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="br0">&#123;</span>
     ...
     <span class="br0">&#125;</span></pre>
<p>

Also see the <a href="../data_types" class="wikilink1" title="data_types">data types</a> page.
</p>

